
= Building

cd path/to/scalp
mkdir build
cd build
cmake -DUSE_GUROBI=ON .. # alternate ccmake ..
make
make install

= Using

After installing, the libraries are found in ./lib/ and the headers are in ./include

= Examples

You can build all examples using
make -C examples build

from the scalp root directory

or you can build and run an specific example with e. g.
make -C examples/simple_gurobi

